Key Match Events: Lillard and Antetokounmpo dominated the third quarter, contributing 22 of the team's 31 points.
The Bucks maintained at least an 11-point cushion for the entire final frame.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Milwaukee Bucks snapped their six-game losing streak with a decisive 123-100 victory over the Utah Jazz.
Others: Damian Lillard dropped 34 points and Giannis Antetokounmpo added 31 as the Milwaukee Bucks took down the Utah Jazz 123-100 on Thursday.
